 (x^2 - x + \frac{1}{4}) + (y^2 - y + \frac{1}{4}) + (z^2 - z + \frac{1}{4}) \ = \frac{3}{4} 
 \Rightarrow \ (x - \frac{1}{2})^2 \ + \ (y - \frac{1}{2})^2 \ + \ (z - \frac{1}{2})^2 \ = \frac{3}{4}  \ \ . 
 \ x = y = z = t \ . 
 \ t + t + t \ = \ 1 \ \Rightarrow \ t \ = \ \frac{1}{3} \ . 
